# Fixture FM2: Percent-encoding in prefixed-name local part is NOT decoded.
#
# Hypothesis: A parser that percent-decodes the local part before appending
# it to the prefix IRI will produce <http://example/café> (non-ASCII IRI).
# The spec requires the percent-encoded form to be passed through unchanged,
# yielding <http://example/caf%C3%A9>.
#
# Expected triple: <http://example/caf%C3%A9> <http://example/p> <http://example/o>
# Divergence signal: ObjectMismatch / FactOnlyIn if one parser decodes and
# the other keeps the percent-encoding.
#
# Spec: Turtle §2.4 — percent-encoded sequences are passed through unchanged.
# Turtle §6.3 PLX ::= PERCENT | PN_LOCAL_ESC; PERCENT ::= '%' HEX HEX.

@prefix ex: <http://example/> .

ex:caf%C3%A9  ex:p   ex:o .
ex:spa%20ce   ex:p   ex:o .
